<div class="wu" style="background:var(--tvp);padding:0;">
  <div class="pdp-tabs"><button class="pdp-tab on" onclick="showTab('desc')">Description</button><button class="pdp-tab" onclick="showTab('det')">Details &amp; dimensions</button><button class="pdp-tab" onclick="showTab('rev')">Reviews (47)</button><button class="pdp-tab" onclick="showTab('sel')">About the seller</button></div>
  <div class="tab-body">
    <div class="tab-pane on" id="td-desc"><p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--cm);line-height:1.8;max-width:580px;margin-bottom:1rem;">Each urn is hand-thrown on the wheel by ceramicist Nora Hayashi in her Portland studio. The sage glaze is fired at high temperature, producing a matte, earthy finish with subtle variation — no two are identical. Designed to hold the cremated remains of one adult, with a threaded lid for secure, dignified closure.</p><p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--cm);line-height:1.8;max-width:580px;">Earthen Studio believes the objects we use to honor our loved ones should be as beautiful and considered as the people themselves. Every piece is made with that intention.</p></div>
    <div class="tab-pane" id="td-det"><div class="det-row"><span>Dimensions</span><span>9.5" H × 5.5" W (standard)</span></div><div class="det-row"><span>Capacity</span><span>200 cubic inches (standard adult)</span></div><div class="det-row"><span>Material</span><span>High-fire stoneware clay</span></div><div class="det-row"><span>Finish</span><span>Matte glaze, hand-applied</span></div><div class="det-row"><span>Closure</span><span>Threaded ceramic lid with felt seal</span></div><div class="det-row"><span>Weight</span><span>Approx. 3.2 lbs empty</span></div><div class="det-row"><span>Ships in</span><span>Padded, biodegradable box</span></div><div class="det-row"><span>Made in</span><span>Portland, Oregon, USA</span></div></div>
    <div class="tab-pane" id="td-rev">
      <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:1.5rem;margin-bottom:1.5rem;padding-bottom:1.2rem;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(44,40,37,.08);">
        <div style="text-align:center;"><div style="font-family:var(--sf);font-size:40px;font-weight:300;color:var(--ch);line-height:1;">4.9</div><div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--tr);">★★★★★</div><div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--cl);">47 reviews</div></div>
        <div style="flex:1;"><div class="rb-row"><span style="font-size:12px;color:var(--cl);width:20px;">5★</span><div class="rb-bg"><div class="rb-f" style="width:85%"></div></div><span style="font-size:11px;color:var(--cl);width:22px;">40</span></div><div class="rb-row"><span style="font-size:12px;color:var(--cl);width:20px;">4★</span><div class="rb-bg"><div class="rb-f" style="width:13%;background:var(--tl)"></div></div><span style="font-size:11px;color:var(--cl);width:22px;">6</span></div><div class="rb-row"><span style="font-size:12px;color:var(--cl);width:20px;">3★</span><div class="rb-bg"><div class="rb-f" style="width:2%;background:var(--cl)"></div></div><span style="font-size:11px;color:var(--cl);width:22px;">1</span></div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="rv-c"><div class="rv-hd"><span class="rv-nm">Diane M., Seattle WA</span><span class="rv-dt">March 2025</span></div><div class="rv-st">★★★★★</div><div class="rv-tx">The quality is extraordinary — it arrived beautifully packed. Nora sent a handwritten note. This is what end of life commerce should look like.</div></div>
      <div class="rv-c"><div class="rv-hd"><span class="rv-nm">Theo R., Austin TX</span><span class="rv-dt">January 2025</span></div><div class="rv-st">★★★★★</div><div class="rv-tx">The craftsmanship feels deeply intentional. It sits on our mantle and gets more beautiful every day.</div></div>
      <div class="rv-c"><div class="rv-hd"><span class="rv-nm">Sandra K., Chicago IL</span><span class="rv-dt">November 2024</span></div><div class="rv-st">★★★★☆</div><div class="rv-tx">Very beautiful. Shipping took slightly longer than expected but Nora communicated throughout. The personalization was perfect.</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="tab-pane" id="td-sel"><div class="sp-card"><div class="sp-av">ES</div><div><div class="sp-nm">Earthen Studio</div><div class="sp-lc">Portland, Oregon · On CodaCo since 2021</div><div class="sp-bio">Nora Hayashi has been throwing functional ceramics for over fifteen years. After losing her own mother, she began making urns as a way of honoring the people who shape us. Every piece is made with intention.</div><div class="sp-sts"><div><div class="sp-sn">214</div><div class="sp-sl">Orders</div></div><div><div class="sp-sn">4.9</div><div class="sp-sl">Avg rating</div></div><div><div class="sp-sn">100%</div><div class="sp-sl">On-time</div></div></div></div></div></div>
